This paper discusses the use of automated reasoning and Description Logics in conceptual data modelling, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of DL reasoners for implementation, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the mapping of ORM2 to DLRifd, which involves ontological aspects of the modelling languages, placing it under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO).
